You need the following files:

    MHELP.CB   -> BRIEF\MACROS\
    MARIO.HLP  -> BRIEF\HELP\


╒════════════╤═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
│Installation│
└────────────┘

To begin with, type CB MHELP.CB within the brief\macros directory.

Install the following line into your initials macro and press ALT-F10
to compile:

autoload("mhelp","mhelp_word","mhelp");     /* .CB format */

or:

(autoload "mhelp" "mhelp_word" "mhelp")     /* .M format */

To assign the quick look-up to a key insert the following line also:
(if you don't wish to assign a key just push F10 and type mhelp or
mhelp_word)

assign_to_key("<Alt-F11>","mhelp_word");
assign_to_key("<Ctrl-F11>","mhelp");

With this set up, place your cursor on a Super FX instruction and
press <Alt-F11> to pop-up the help window.  <Tab> allows you to select
a reference to look at, <Enter> views it.

